4 A BILL FOR AN ACT ENTITLED: “AN ACT INCREASING THE AMOUNT OF PROFESIONAL STIPENDS PAID
5 TO TEACHERS HOLDING NATIONAL BOARD FOR PROFESSIONAL TEACHING STANDARDS
6 CERTIFICATION AND PROVIDING A MECHANISM FOR ANNUAL INFLATIONARY ADJUSTMENT TO THE
7 STIPENDS; AMENDING SECTION 20-4-134, MCA; AND PROVIDING AN EFFECTIVE DATE AND AN
8 APPLICABILITY DATE.”
9
10 BE IT ENACTED BY THE LEGISLATURE OF THE STATE OF MONTANA:
11
12 Section 1. Section 20-4-134, MCA, is amended to read:
13 "20-4-134. Professional stipends for teachers certified by national board for professional
14 teaching standards. (1) Pursuant to subsection (5), an annual stipend of up to $1,500 an amount equivalent to
15 50% of the quality educator payment amount provided in 20-9-306 for the applicable year must be provided to
16 each teacher who holds a current certificate from the national board for professional teaching standards if the
17 teacher is:
18 (a) a full-time classroom teacher, librarian, or other full-time employee serving in an assignment
19 covered by national board certification assessment;
20 (b) certified to teach in Montana under the provisions of 20-4-103; and
21 (c) a full-time employee of:
22 (i) a Montana public school district, as defined in 20-6-101;
23 (ii) an education cooperative, as described in 20-7-451;
24 (iii) the Montana school for the deaf and blind, as described in 20-8-101; or
25 (iv) a correctional facility, as defined in 41-5-103.
26 (2) An annual stipend of up to $2,500 an amount equivalent to 85% of the quality educator
27 payment amount provided in 20-9-306 for the applicable year must be provided to each teacher who meets the
28 criteria for the stipend in subsection (1) and who has an instructional assignment in a school identified as:
