1 (a) a school in a high-poverty area eligible to participate in the community eligibility provision under
2 Public Law 111-296; or
3 (b) an impacted school as defined in 20-4-502.
4 (3) A teacher becomes eligible for the stipend in subsection (1) in the school year beginning July 1
5 after the teacher obtains certification or recertification from the national board for professional teaching
6 standards.
7 (4) By March 1, the superintendent of public instruction shall distribute stipend payments to any
8 entity listed in subsections (1)(c)(i) through (1)(c)(iv) that employs an eligible teacher.
9 (5) The obligation for funding a portion of the professional stipends is an obligation of the state.
10 This section may not be construed to require a school district to provide its matching portion of a stipend to a
11 qualifying teacher without a payment from the state to the district. If the money appropriated for the stipends is
12 not enough to provide the full amount for each eligible teacher, the superintendent of public instruction shall
13 request the state budget director to submit a request for a supplemental appropriation in the second year of the
14 biennium that is sufficient to complete the funding of the stipends.
15 (6) (a) For a stipend under subsection (1), the state shall pay $500 50% of the maximum stipend
16 amount under subsection (1) and another $1 1% of the amount for each $1 1% of the amount contributed by
17 the teacher's school district, up to a maximum state contribution of $1,000 75% of the amount.
18 (b) For a stipend under subsection (2), the state shall pay $1,000 55% of the maximum stipend
19 amount under subsection (2) and another $2 2% of the amount for each $1 1% of the amount contributed by
20 the teacher's school district, up to a maximum state contribution of $2,000 85% of the amount."
21
22 NEW SECTION. Section 2. Effective date. [This act] is effective July 1, 2025.
23
24 NEW SECTION. Section 3. Applicability. [This act] applies to stipends paid for school years
25 beginning on or after July 1, 2025.
